Justice minister Ronald Lamola told the SA Human Rights Commission “the wheels of justice were turning” within his ministry during the time of the July 2021 unrest and after as they continue to deal with ongoing cases. Lamola was testifying at the Gauteng leg of the hearings into the  unrest which claimed the lives of more than  300 people and cost the economy billions of rand in damage. Listen: According to Lamola, his ministry remains committed to  finding the “ringleaders, plotters and instigators” behind the unrest. TimesLIVE